snippet: After two rounds of voting at the General Assembly, the five new rotating members will be Angola, Malaysia, New Zealand, Spain and Venezuela.
abstract: Venezuela secures seat on United Nations Security Council, despite objections by United States; Turkey, vital and complicated American ally, is resoundingly defeated in voting.
lead_paragraph: After two rounds of voting at the General Assembly, the five new rotating members will be Angola, Malaysia, New Zealand, Spain and Venezuela.

headline.main: Venezuela Gets U.N. Seat; Turkey Is Denied
headline.print_headline: Venezuela Gets U.N. Seat; Turkey Is Denied
